description:
The Price Adjustment Service API is intended to provide a common service for other services and applications to build a price adjustment system for discounts and fees.

The API is composed of two main entities: Price Adjustments and Price Adjustment Associations.

A Price Adjustment is a discount or fee; as well as the amount. Alone, it does nothing since it is not associated to any items.
  - This entity contains the type of adjustment, the amount of the adjustment, and other information that will be shared by all the Price Adjustment Associations that refer to it.
  - Newly created Price Adjustments will have no Price Adjustment Associations associated with them by default.
  - Updating a Price Adjustment will also soft-update Price Adjustment Associations that refer to it, since the information they refer to will have been updated.
  - Deleting a Price Adjustment will delete all the Price Adjustment Associations that refer to it, since they should not apply a non-existant Price Adjustment to anything.

A Price Adjustment Association is the link between a Price Adjustment and the items the Price Adjustment applies to. Together, they make up the actual discount or fee that would be applied.
 - This entity contains the type of association, the items that the association applies to, and other information about the association itself.

To ground this in a complete example:

```
  POST /commerce/stores/{storeId}/price-adjustments
  // -> creates a new Price Adjustment
  // -> but, we have nothing associated with it yet!
  // -> so it will never apply to an item/category
  // -> to do that, we need to create an association

  POST /commerce/stores/{storeId}/price-adjustment-associations
  // -> creates a new Price Adjustment Association
  // -> now we are associated, and it will apply!
```
